Loushanna Craig had gone to Tenerife with her husband for three-day holiday but her biometric ID card was stolen . 
  She was refused to fly home over fears she was an illegal immigrant . 
  Mrs Craig was marooned on the island for up to two weeks after her card was taken . 
  She has a Jamaican passport but has 'right to remain' status in the UK . 
  Ryanair refused to accept her ID card as a substitute for her passport . 
  She travelled to Madrid but was stopped at the airport by police . 
 